episodes.title: Who Shot Mr. Burns? Part Two
episodes.plot: Mr. Burns is laying in the hospital while the investigation into his shooter begins. Every citizen has motivation, but it's Simpson DNA that has been found.

episodes.title: Radioactive Man
episodes.plot: Milhouse is cast as Radioactive Man's sidekick in a Hollywood production of the comic book.

episodes.title: Home Sweet Home-Dum-Diddly Doodily
episodes.plot: Marge and Homer lose custody of the kids, who are sent to live at the Flanders' house.

episodes.title: Bart Sells His Soul
episodes.plot: Bart casually sells his soul to Milhouse for $5 but soon regrets it; Moe converts his dank bar into a family restaurant.

episodes.title: Lisa the Vegetarian
episodes.plot: A trip to a local petting zoo convinces Lisa to give up meat, despite excessive pressure to convince her not to do so.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror VI
episodes.plot: A lightning storm causes giant advertising mascots to come to life; The children are terrorized by Groundskeeper Willie in their dreams; Homer finds himself trapped in another dimension.

episodes.title: King Size Homer
episodes.plot: Homer intentionally gains more weight in order to qualify for disability and work from home, but soon realizes that being morbidly obese comes with its own problems.

episodes.title: Mother Simpson
episodes.plot: After faking his own death, Homer is reunited with his mother, who harbors a deep secret.

episodes.title: Sideshow Bob's Last Gleaming
episodes.plot: Sideshow Bob again escapes from prison and takes control of a TV screen at an air show, demanding all television stations immediately go off the air.

episodes.title: The Simpsons 138th Episode Spectacular!
episodes.plot: Troy McClure hosts a retrospective of the first 137 episodes of The Simpsons (1989).

episodes.title: Marge Be Not Proud
episodes.plot: Marge's relationship with Bart is strained when he is caught shoplifting before Christmas.

episodes.title: Team Homer
episodes.plot: Homer starts a bowling team with Moe, Apu and Otto, but Mr. Burns insists on joining after learning that the team was funded with his money; Springfield Elementary introduces uniforms.

episodes.title: Two Bad Neighbors
episodes.plot: Former President George Bush and his wife, Barbara, move into the Simpsons' neighborhood and soon clash with Bart and Homer.

episodes.title: Scenes from the Class Struggle in Springfield
episodes.plot: After buying a Chanel suit at a bargain price, Marge finds herself invited to a country club by a former schoolmate. Taken in by the opulence of the place, she is soon overcome by a desperation to fit in.

episodes.title: Bart the Fink
episodes.plot: Krusty the Clown is left almost broke after Bart inadvertently rats him out to the IRS, forcing Krusty to take drastic action.

episodes.title: Lisa the Iconoclast
episodes.plot: Lisa may figure out what to do when she discovers that Springfield's founding father was actually a murderous thief while researching for an essay.

episodes.title: Homer the Smithers
episodes.plot: When Smithers is forced to take a vacation, he appoints Homer as his temporary replacement.

episodes.title: The Day the Violence Died
episodes.plot: Bart and Lisa meet a vagabond who claims to be the creator of Itchy from "Itchy and Scratchy."

episodes.title: A Fish Called Selma
episodes.plot: Washed-up movie star Troy McClure starts dating Selma in an attempt to silence bizarre rumors about his personal life and resuscitate his career.

episodes.title: Bart on the Road
episodes.plot: Bart makes a fake driver's license and takes Milhouse, Martin and Nelson on a huge road trip; Lisa spends time with Homer at the power plant.

episodes.title: 22 Short Films About Springfield
episodes.plot: A series of vignettes highlights a day in the life of various Springfield residents.

episodes.title: Raging Abe Simpson and His Grumbling Grandson in 'The Curse of the Flying Hellfish'
episodes.plot: One of Grampa's old war buddies dies, and it's revealed that Mr. Burns is the only other living member of his WWII squad and things go sour quickly.

episodes.title: Much Apu About Nothing
episodes.plot: Anti-immigration fever sweeps Springfield, which threatens to lead to the deportation of Apu, until Homer decides to reject the mob mentality and help him become a legal citizen.

episodes.title: Homerpalooza
episodes.plot: In an attempt to prove his coolness to the kids, Homer takes them to a music festival but ends up embarrassing them after being hired in a sideshow.

episodes.title: Summer of 4'2"
episodes.plot: After realizing how unpopular she is, a disillusioned Lisa sees the vacation to Ned Flanders' beach house as an opportunity to reinvent herself.
